From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ChatGPT <chatgpt@openai.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Cache PBR raster draw resources

Stop creating PBR uniform buffers, joint buffers, material buffers and bind
groups for every mesh on every frame.  Keep one cached resource packet per
PBR draw slot, grow joint buffers only when needed, and update buffer contents
with queue.write_buffer.

This is an intermediate low-risk optimization.  It preserves the current
shader ABI and draw order while removing the worst CPU/driver allocation churn
from the raster path.  A later patch can move this to true instance-buffer
batching.
